******************************************************************************
aspFrame('make', n<,'vert'/'horiz'/'auto'>) - make n frames. Defailt 'auto' 
aspFrame('make', 'nxm') - make n by m frames
aspFrame('overlay') - overlay all frames
aspFrame('show') - redisplay all frames
aspFrame('clear') - clear active frame
aspFrame('close') - delete active frame
aspFrame('closeAll') - delete all frames (restore to a single frame)

aspFrame('annoTop') - toggle z-order of annotation layer and spectrum layer 
aspFrame('annoTop',1/0) - 1 to display annotation layer over spectrum layer
			  0 to display spectrum layer over annotaion layer 

aspFrame('pixmax'):$pixwd - return pixel width of display box (cell)
aspFrame('pixmax2'):$pixwd - return pixel height of display box (cell)
aspFrame('pix2val', pix):$value - give x pixel position, return ppm value
aspFrame('pix2val2', pix):$value - give y pixel position, return ppm or intensity value
aspFrame('val2pix', pix):$value - give ppm value, return x pixel position
aspFrame('val2pix2', pix):$value - give ppm or intensity value, return y pixel position
aspFrame('pix2mm', pix):$value - give x pixel position, return x mm value 
aspFrame('pix2mm2', pix):$value - give y pixel position, return y mm value 
aspFrame('mm2pix', pix):$value - give x mm value, return x pixel position
aspFrame('mm2pix2', pix):$value - give y mm value, return y pixel position

******************************************************************************

Double click to activate a frame.
Move mouse near border to select and move active frame. 
drag corner to resize active frame.

set mfShowPlotterbox = 1 to show frame border 
set mfShowPlotterbox = 0 to hide frame border 

Commands are executed in the active frame. 
May load different spectral data to different frame. 
Each frame have has its own display parameters
